1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:03,340
Can animals and people live in Antarctica?
动物和人类能够在南极洲存活吗

2
00:00:03,980 --> 00:00:08,920
Birds, seals, and whales have a shield against cold air and water.
鸟   海豹以及鲸鱼都有自己的庇护所来抵挡寒风和水

3
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:14,000
Birds have feathers that trap warm air near their bodies for warmth.
鸟的羽毛可以维持自己身体的热量

4
00:00:14,390 --> 00:00:18,920
Seals have fur and a layer of fat that hold in warmth.
海豹的皮毛以及一层脂肪可以让他们保持温暖

5
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:24,040
Early explorers had a hard time with the harsh setting.
早期的探险家们在严酷的环境下度过了艰难的时光

6
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:30,500
Lives were lost from lack of food and from being exposed to cold weather.
很多人因为缺乏食物和暴露在寒冷的天气中而丧失生命.

7
00:00:31,520 --> 00:00:34,930
Today people know how to prepare to live there.
如今人们已经懂得如何在那里生活了

8
00:00:35,510 --> 00:00:39,390
Warmer materials have been made for clothing and shelter.
保温材料被用来制作衣服和建造庇护所

9
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:42,760
But humans still have a difficult time.
但人们的生活依然艰难

10
00:00:42,830 --> 00:00:43,790
Did you know?...
   你知道吗

11
00:00:43,820 --> 00:00:48,360
Interesting facts about how animals survive in Antarctica
南极洲的动物们如何生存的趣闻

12
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:51,670
Animal   Feature
   动物    特点

13
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:54,750
Animal: Penguins
   动物    企鹅

14
00:00:55,330 --> 00:01:01,270
Feature: have a thick layer of packed waterproof feathers to keep them warm.
特点   拥有一层厚厚的防水羽毛以保暖

15
00:01:01,860 --> 00:01:04,420
Animal: Insects
   动物   昆虫

16
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:10,740
Feature: have natural antifreeze in their blood to keep them from freezing.
特点   在它们血液中有天然的防冻物质以抵抗寒冷

17
00:01:11,490 --> 00:01:14,160
Animal: Seals
动物   海豹

18
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:20,920
Feature: are born with white fur to help them blend into the ice and snow.
特点   与生俱来的白色的皮毛能够帮助它们适应冰雪环境

19
00:01:21,770 --> 00:01:24,680
Animal: Polar Bears
动物   北极熊

20
00:01:25,260 --> 00:01:31,290
Feature: have thick claws to help them dig into the ice so they don't slip.
特点   厚厚的爪子能够帮助它们牢牢抓住冰面而不至于滑动

